explanation:
- OS_ForEachObjectOfType: Direct callee in OS_DeleteAllObjects; must be inspected to see whether it (or the callbacks it invokes) uses memcmp to compare object names (null-terminated strings).
- OS_ForEachObject: Direct callee in OS_DeleteAllObjects; it calls OS_ForEachObjectOfType and may perform name/comparison operations internally.
- OS_CleanUpObject: Callback passed into the iterator functions; this is a prime candidate to perform string comparisons (e.g. object name checks) and therefore must be checked for memcmp usage.
- OS_TaskDelay: Direct callee (used between attempts); include to check transitive calls that could use memcmp (via OS_TaskDelay_Impl or test stubs).
- OS_TaskDelay_Impl: The implementation called by OS_TaskDelay; include to inspect any string-comparison usage.
- OS_ObjectIdIteratorInit: Callee of OS_ForEachObjectOfType; iterator initialization code may compare names/strings and could call memcmp.
- OS_ObjectIdIteratorProcessEntry: Iterator body used by OS_ForEachObjectOfType; likely location for entry-level comparisons (may call memcmp).
- OS_ObjectIdIteratorDestroy: Iterator cleanup; include to be thorough for any string-comparison use in iterator lifecycle.
- UT_ExecuteBasicHandler: Appears in the static call graph as a callee; test-stub handler code often contains helper comparisons—must be checked for memcmp usage invoked transitively.
- UT_Stub_RegisterContextWithMetaData: Registered by iterator/TaskDelay/test stubs in the graph; could contain string comparisons (test harness code) that use memcmp.
- UT_Stub_RegisterReturnType: Part of the UT stub machinery called transitively by OS_TaskDelay; include to inspect for memcmp in test stubs.
- UT_Stub_GetReturnValuePtr: UT stub helper that may compare identifiers/names internally; include to ensure no memcmp-on-strings.
- UT_GetStubEntry: Part of UT_ExecuteBasicHandler call chain; include to inspect stub lookup/comparison code for memcmp usage.
- UT_SetHandlerFunction: UT handler setup routine that could perform string-based comparisons; include for completeness.
- UT_DefaultStubImpl: Default UT stub implementation used by UT_ExecuteBasicHandler; inspect for any memcmp usage.
- memcmp: The standard-library function in question — include the symbol so the analyzer can find all call-sites and verify whether any of the above functions call memcmp to compare null-terminated strings.

Why these are needed: OS_DeleteAllObjects itself contains no string operations, but it invokes iterators and a cleanup callback (and transitively test-stub helpers) that are the likely places where string comparisons could occur. To determine a MISRA violation (memcmp used to compare null-terminated strings) you must inspect these callees and the memcmp symbol to find any call-sites and verify the argument usage (whether the operands are C-style null-terminated strings).
